<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_e7920812-7f26-4363-b653-cd79108162d0" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="NSW"><sptc>B2P12</sptc><title id="_9dc52d92-9bc5-48d5-919a-3a54b970e8fc">Water efficiency</title><subclause id="_54d8307b-7571-47e6-bb6c-666d98b916eb" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_00b16f98-d914-4a12-a403-72d0f2a08b68">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p> A <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1334_0.4.0.xml#_92b3a3dc-59e4-425f-909b-d8eb03e6460a" id="_0205fb4d-ff21-4f0e-8346-9d7ad002991a" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">heated water</xref> service must ensure the efficient use of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1250_0.7.0.xml#_762d6a54-e28c-400b-b9c5-5fceac019a05" id="_c7c7d4f7-7c33-4cdb-90bf-273cd5a99c2e" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">drinking water</xref> by limiting water use from a tap or outlet for a shower, basin, kitchen sink or laundry trough to a flow rate of not more than 9 l/m.</p></subclause><callout id="_a5983798-7cae-4895-a49d-b65e573a5d1a"><callout-type ncc-info-type="info"/><p>In New South Wales, fixtures, tapware and appliances installed within new Class 1 and 2 Buildings are subject to the water efficiency targets regulated under BASIX</p></callout></clause>